#!/usr/bin/env python3
"""
computer-use — Universal Desktop + Browser Automation CLI
========================================================

A standalone tool that any agent (Claude Code, OpenClaw, OpenCode, etc.)
can call for desktop and browser automation. All output is JSON.

Two channels:
  - Native ops: cliclick (mouse/keyboard), screencapture, Apple Vision OCR,
    macOS Accessibility API — works on any Mac app.
  - Browser CDP: connects to Chrome via chrome.debugger (extension mode)
    or WebSocket remote debugging port — works on browser content.

Usage:
  computer-use screenshot                    Full-screen screenshot
  computer-use screenshot --ocr              Full-screen screenshot + OCR
  computer-use screenshot --window "App"     Capture a specific window
  computer-use screenshot --window "App" --ocr  Window screenshot + OCR
  computer-use ocr <image_path>              Run Apple Vision OCR on image
  computer-use tree                          Get AX tree of frontmost app
  computer-use click <x> <y>                 Physical click at screen coords
  computer-use click --ocr <x> <y>          Click using OCR pixel coords (Retina auto-convert)
  computer-use type <text>                   Type text at current focus
  computer-use key <shortcut>                Press key combo (e.g. cmd+r)
  computer-use scroll <dx> [dy]              Scroll at current position
  computer-use mouse <x> <y>                 Move mouse to screen coords
  computer-use mouse --ocr <x> <y>          Move mouse using OCR pixel coords
  computer-use position                      Get current mouse position
  computer-use calibrate                     Show display scale factor + coordinate info

  computer-use chrome-js <expr>              Execute JS via CDP (no hang)
  computer-use cdp-click <selector>          Browser click by CSS selector
  computer-use cdp-type <selector> <text>     Browser fill input
  computer-use cdp-screenshot                Browser page screenshot (base64)
  computer-use cdp-file <selector> <path>     Browser file input
  computer-use cdp-eval <js>                 Browser evaluate JS
  computer-use cdp-scroll <dx> [dy]          Browser scroll
  computer-use cdp-interactive               List all interactive elements

  computer-use start-chrome                  Launch Chrome with debug port
  computer-use serve [--port PORT]           HTTP server for agent integration

Environment:
  CU_CDP_PORT  Chrome remote debugging port (default 9222)
  CU_NATIVE    Path to native bridge (default auto-detect)
"""

